Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.07,0:00:02.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0100,,{\c&HFFFF&}"Closed Circle."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.52,0:00:08.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0100,,{\c&HFFFF&}Being isolated from the outside world,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.70,0:00:12.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0100,,{\c&HFFFF&}the culprit is trapped among people in the same location and situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.19,0:00:16.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0100,,{\c&HFFFF&}intervention by police and scientific investigation are impossible,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.24,0:00:21.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0100,,{\c&HFFFF&}and the answer must be reached purely by logical methods of thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.64,0:00:28.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0100,,{\c&HFFFF&}In other words, the detectives in attendance are on the same standing as you who are viewing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.39,0:00:32.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0100,,{\c&HFFFF&}Everyone, can you unmask the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.95,0:00:35.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0100,,{\be10}It doesn't matter how many times you try,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.72,0:00:37.84,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0100,,{\be10}whether it's in love, deductions, today, or tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.84,0:00:39.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0100,,{\be10}The true killer lurking in the shadows...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.60,0:00:41.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0100,,{\be10}The Hatamoto family's painful secret!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.56,0:00:43.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0100,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.18,0:00:44.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0100,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.97,0:00:47.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0100,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.92,0:02:22.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0100,,{\fad(400,400)\c&HCFCFCF}"Detective Conan" is brought to you by these sponsors.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.35,0:02:31.12,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We were nearly stranded on an island
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.12,0:02:34.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}before we were picked up by a ship that the Hatamoto family had reserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.92,0:02:39.36,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Including the three of us and the butler, there were only ten people onboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.36,0:02:41.43,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}On our way back to land, Gozo Hatamoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.43,0:02:44.57,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}head of the Hatamoto family, was murdered in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.57,0:02:46.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The main suspect was Takeshi Hatamoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.37,0:02:48.87,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}who entered the family by marrying Natsue Hatamoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.87,0:02:51.41,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He turned out to be the son of Isao Zaiki,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.41,0:02:56.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}who killed himself after Gozo took over his company 10 years earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.04,0:03:00.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Since he had a motive, everyone decided to lock Takeshi in a storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.18,0:03:04.49,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It looked like the case was closed, but there was more to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.49,0:03:07.99,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Tatsuo Hatamoto, Akie's husband, was found dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.99,0:03:10.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and Takeshi had escaped from the storeroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.92,0:03:22.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuo!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.62,0:03:24.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.37,0:03:26.70,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Akie Hatamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:25.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.62,0:03:28.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This never would've happened
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.62,0:03:31.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,if you hadn't brought Takeshi into our family!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.33,0:03:32.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you have to say for yourself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.58,0:03:36.29,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,400)\move(244,482,124,482)}Kitaro Hatamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.58,0:03:36.29,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,400)\move(632,482,512,482)}Ichiro Hatamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.46,0:03:34.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You certainly are lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.90,0:03:41.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s killed Father, all of his fortune belongs to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.55,0:03:41.30,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(200,0)\move(726,482,606,482)}Mariko Hatamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.74,0:03:45.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't be serious! I don't care about his fortune!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.64,0:03:49.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're still not certain that Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the one responsible, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.48,0:03:53.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.55,0:03:58.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The storeroom door was unlocked when we checked it out, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.02,0:04:00.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.02,0:04:02.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't have gotten out
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.29,0:04:03.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,unless someone unlocked it from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.89,0:04:05.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.86,0:04:07.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no signs of damage on the door, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.96,0:04:10.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So if someone did unlock it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.43,0:04:12.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then he has an accomplice in this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.67,0:04:26.47,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi Hatamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.08,0:04:30.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So let me get this straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.38,0:04:33.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time of Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.14,0:04:36.60,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Joji Hatamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.72,0:04:37.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the three of you were alone in your private rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.46,0:04:41.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while you two were together in your shared room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.13,0:04:45.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I couldn't sleep, so I went for a little walk...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.03,0:04:47.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that just like the first murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.70,0:04:50.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,aside from everyone who was with Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.71,0:04:52.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,nobody here has an alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.71,0:04:56.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta be kidding me! My husband just died!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.68,0:04:59.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why am {\i1}I{\i0} a suspect?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.95,0:05:04.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're{\i0} the one who's happiest to see him dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.49,0:05:10.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that you've been seeing other men!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.22,0:05:14.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You{\i0} had a big enough reason to kill Grandfather!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.20,0:05:17.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who wanted his inheritance the most!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.70,0:05:21.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, you two! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.07,0:05:27.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you draw that, Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.64,0:05:30.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.31,0:05:33.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And your son Ichiro isn't exempt either!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.31,0:05:35.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.18,0:05:36.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he was pretty pissed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.95,0:05:40.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after Grandfather tore up his prize-winning drawing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.39,0:05:44.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was Father's fault—he never recognized this boy's talent!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.83,0:05:47.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuo always made fun of you, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.73,0:05:50.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Depressed introvert" and stuff like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.06,0:05:53.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I didn't kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.47,0:05:57.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one who wanted to be free of Grandfather the most...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.51,0:06:00.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...was you, Uncle Kitaro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.21,0:06:01.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.94,0:06:03.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro! Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.88,0:06:04.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.95,0:06:06.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be alright by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.75,0:06:11.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine. I'm not a weakling like my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.52,0:06:12.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.89,0:06:15.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mr. Butler...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.29,0:06:18.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen between Kitaro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.56,0:06:23.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kitaro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} has wanted to leave the Hatamoto family for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.26,0:06:27.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He says he doesn't have the ambition to run the family company.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.03,0:06:30.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the master was greatly opposed to the idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.70,0:06:32.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But even if {\i1}he{\i0} wasn't against it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.97,0:06:36.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think his wife Mariko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} would have allowed it either...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.05,0:06:41.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.85,0:06:45.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been 20 minutes, but Ichiro still isn't back from the restroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.85,0:06:47.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me Takeshi got him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.49,0:06:54.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down! Stay where you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.63,0:06:58.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! But Ichiro isn't back yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.07,0:06:59.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.07,0:07:01.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't leave the room, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.87,0:07:03.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Ran and Conan! Are you there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.94,0:07:05.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.17,0:07:06.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.61,0:07:08.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to the electrical room!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.44,0:07:11.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You two head for the restroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.01,0:07:14.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The restrooms were this way, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.18,0:07:18.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't that Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s voice?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.35,0:07:19.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.16,0:07:23.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.73,0:07:27.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.56,0:07:29.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-My leg!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.36,0:07:31.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there, Ichiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.27,0:07:32.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's alright! The wound isn't deep!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.93,0:07:34.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to bandage it up right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.57,0:07:37.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get the first-aid kit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.44,0:07:39.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who did this to you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.47,0:07:40.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.67,0:07:45.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The lights suddenly went out and then I sensed someone come in...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.28,0:07:47.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then they stabbed me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.25,0:07:51.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.45,0:07:55.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...{\i1}my{\i0} knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.36,0:07:57.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me {\i1}you{\i0} did this, Joji!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.36,0:07:59.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.49,0:08:02.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was with you all in the dining room\Nwhen the power went out!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.30,0:08:03.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't have done this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.90,0:08:05.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.50,0:08:09.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There is only one person who could have done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.07,0:08:10.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.97,0:08:13.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not necessarily the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.97,0:08:17.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Ran take care of Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s bandage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.28,0:08:21.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like the rest of you to come to the electrical room with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.02,0:08:25.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.22,0:08:28.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Have a look for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.49,0:08:31.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.02,0:08:33.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a type of timing device.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.09,0:08:36.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This one is simple enough for anyone to set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.00,0:08:39.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You attach a heavy weight to the breaker,\Nbalance it around a fulcrum,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.50,0:08:42.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then put a candle in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.47,0:08:46.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After enough time passes, the rope burns apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.57,0:08:49.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,which causes the weight to pull down on the breaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.28,0:08:51.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from how much of the candle has melted,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.58,0:08:53.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,this was all set up quite a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.91,0:08:59.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, any one of you could be\Nresponsible for the power outage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.29,0:09:03.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, I'll take the responsibility of finding Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.29,0:09:07.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I do, I don't want any of you\Nto take a step out of the dining room!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.68,0:09:17.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not in Kitaro's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.22,0:09:22.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These two seem to have rather different personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.92,0:09:24.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is their marriage holding up well?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.89,0:09:28.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. They're both cousins, and although it may not look like it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.76,0:09:32.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,they've been good friends since they were little.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.03,0:09:34.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-They're cousins and they're married?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.70,0:09:36.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.94,0:09:40.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the master was extremely opposed to them, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.41,0:09:42.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"Them, too"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.58,0:09:51.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't look like he's in Joji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.69,0:09:54.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is this his knife case?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.92,0:09:56.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.02,0:10:02.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Two of his knives are missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.06,0:10:03.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.20,0:10:07.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One knife we found right after Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was attacked,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.20,0:10:09.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but where's the other one?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.67,0:10:13.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This must be Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.67,0:10:15.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? These are his drawings!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.91,0:10:18.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's no reason to enter the room carelessly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.45,0:10:22.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} could be hiding in here with a weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.02,0:10:24.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, he's really good!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.45,0:10:28.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows, maybe there's a drawing of the murder scene here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.49,0:10:31.12,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.73,0:10:37.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, don't touch those!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.78,0:10:38.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.24,0:10:44.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not in here, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.25,0:10:46.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.24,0:10:48.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.04,0:10:50.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Charcoal. You use it for rough sketches.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.84,0:10:52.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.18,0:10:54.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an ordinary eraser.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.17,0:10:57.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.62,0:11:02.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't in our rooms or in Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.95,0:11:06.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left is Akie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room here...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.29,0:11:11.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess he's not on the ship anymore—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.43,0:11:14.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.83,0:11:17.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Nothing at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.57,0:11:18.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.90,0:11:22.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's return to the dining room for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.01,0:11:28.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey! Mr. Butler!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.35,0:11:29.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know if...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.72,0:11:34.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did that ever happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.32,0:11:39.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you find out?\NOnly the master and I know about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.46,0:11:41.93,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So I'm right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.93,0:11:44.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The first incident, in which Mr. Gozo was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.66,0:11:49.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The bread found near the body,\Nand the location of the murder weapon...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.37,0:11:51.94,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The second incident, in which Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.94,0:11:55.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The splash and thud sounds\NI heard at the time of the murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.74,0:11:58.94,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The person who unlocked the storeroom door...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.94,0:12:03.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And then the third incident, in which Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was stabbed in the dark...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.92,0:12:06.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Each of these mysteries is connected by a single thread!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.08,0:12:17.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, come here a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.48,0:12:20.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.88,0:12:22.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.89,0:12:31.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.73,0:12:35.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.53,0:12:37.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He has something important to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.23,0:12:41.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he wants everyone to come to Akie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room in 10 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.37,0:12:43.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something important to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.97,0:12:45.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell the others!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.98,0:12:51.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Come on! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.95,0:12:54.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The old man's voice is #59...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.82,0:12:57.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know who did it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.85,0:13:03.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Someone on this ship was responsible for all three incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.29,0:13:05.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.69,0:13:07.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's obviously him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.60,0:13:09.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Takeshi's doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.16,0:13:11.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, just calm down...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.07,0:13:15.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Before I reveal the killer's name, let us look at the incidents again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.70,0:13:18.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First was Incident #1, in which\NMr. Gozo was murdered in his room,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.74,0:13:21.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,which had been locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.94,0:13:24.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From the fact that there was blood on the doorframe,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.48,0:13:28.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Gozo likely escaped back into his room after he was stabbed outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.08,0:13:33.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He then locked the door, but fell lifeless soon after.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.22,0:13:36.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We later found a flower on the ground, in front of the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.66,0:13:40.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Takeshi was wearing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.20,0:13:41.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means he did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.90,0:13:44.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there is one strange detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.80,0:13:48.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though Mr. Gozo was stabbed outside his room,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.04,0:13:50.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there were no blood marks in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.57,0:13:52.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure the killer didn't wipe it up
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.57,0:13:55.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to delay us from discovering the corpse?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.61,0:13:57.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not refuting that fact;
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.01,0:14:01.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just saying that the flower fell\N{\i1}after{\i0} the blood was wiped up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.35,0:14:03.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand if the killer accidentally dropped it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.52,0:14:05.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while stabbing the victim and then escaping...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.72,0:14:08.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the killer meticulously wiped up the blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.46,0:14:12.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By leaving the flower there, everyone would've noticed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.16,0:14:15.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially if it was dropped during the middle of cleaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.36,0:14:19.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the killer purposely left the flower on the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.07,0:14:22.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to make Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} look guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.14,0:14:26.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next is Incident #2, in which Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered on the deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.41,0:14:28.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike the first incident with its flower
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.98,0:14:32.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the third incident with its fancy set-up,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.01,0:14:35.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,this incident lacked any sort of artificiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.28,0:14:37.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If these were all indeed done by the same person,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.95,0:14:45.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,my guess is that the second murder was an unplanned one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.13,0:14:48.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, {\i1}why{\i0} was Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} murdered?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.80,0:14:52.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer to that question is in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.30,0:14:55.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my knife case!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.10,0:14:58.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a look. Two knives are missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.17,0:15:01.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found one of them at the scene of Incident #3,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.35,0:15:03.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but where did the other one go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.21,0:15:07.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The main point here is in the two sounds that Conan heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.82,0:15:11.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The thud was likely the sound of the killer striking Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.69,0:15:15.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but what was the splash that came before it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.02,0:15:16.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's what I'm thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.79,0:15:21.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The splash sound was the other knife from this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.80,0:15:24.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} just happened to see it thrown overboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.80,0:15:27.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer could have killed him to keep things quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.80,0:15:30.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That would make the most sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.01,0:15:34.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Takeshi vanished from the storeroom after the second incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.81,0:15:37.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Takeshi is the most suspicious here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.68,0:15:42.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that storeroom door was locked from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.08,0:15:44.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Escape would have been impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.25,0:15:45.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,unless someone unlocked it for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.52,0:15:47.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was it, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.26,0:15:48.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who opened it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.96,0:15:51.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.89,0:15:54.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s murder wasn't part of the killer's plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.43,0:15:58.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and it took place while Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was locked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.00,0:16:00.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer worked so hard to make Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} look guilty,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.87,0:16:04.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but this second murder would do just the opposite and prove his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.77,0:16:08.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the killer unlocked the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.68,0:16:11.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This was done to make it look like Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.11,0:16:14.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,had the ability to murder Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.02,0:16:17.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Then why did Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} run away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.12,0:16:19.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! We {\i1}still{\i0} haven't found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.65,0:16:22.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have him explain that himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.59,0:16:27.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Why don't you stop hiding and come out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.46,0:16:30.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in this room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.73,0:16:33.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.19,0:16:39.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.83,0:16:44.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, tell us what happened when you escaped from the storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.63,0:16:48.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I thought something happened to Natsue...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.27,0:16:50.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't stand around doing nothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.07,0:16:53.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and as I was pounding on the door,\Nit suddenly unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.27,0:16:55.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I ran out of there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.14,0:16:57.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then when I went up to the deck...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.48,0:17:00.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi did it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.18,0:17:02.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatsuo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.22,0:17:04.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Realizing that I would be blamed again,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.79,0:17:08.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I ran into Akie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room,\Nwhose door just happened to be open.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.09,0:17:11.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I stayed inside the closet the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.09,0:17:14.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the person who stabbed Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} during Incident #3
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.16,0:17:16.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,wasn't him either...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.10,0:17:17.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.70,0:17:20.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would they do something this horrible to Ichiro?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.20,0:17:24.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the killer made a big mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.37,0:17:25.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.31,0:17:29.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Unlocking the storeroom door.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.44,0:17:32.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer had managed to frame Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.45,0:17:36.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but now it looked like he had an accomplice who had let him out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.72,0:17:40.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't until then that anyone started to suspect the real killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.85,0:17:44.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Flustered, the murderer came up with a scheme
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.16,0:17:46.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to avoid any further suspicion:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.33,0:17:51.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...Incident #3, in which Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was attacked in the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.33,0:17:57.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was in this incident that the killer dug his own grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.77,0:18:02.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In the darkness, the killer shouldn't have been able to see Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.44,0:18:06.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, he was clearly able to see Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} well enough to stab him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.78,0:18:08.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.78,0:18:12.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, the weapon was found lying at the scene of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.09,0:18:17.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike the first two incidents,\Nthe attacker didn't leave with the weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.96,0:18:21.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the attacker {\i1}couldn't{\i0} have left with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.20,0:18:25.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, he couldn't go anywhere with his injured leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.47,0:18:29.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean to say—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.30,0:18:30.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.44,0:18:33.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who stabbed him...was Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.77,0:18:38.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one who killed Mr. Gozo and Tatsuo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.41,0:18:43.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...was you, Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.32,0:18:46.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.65,0:18:48.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason you put the lights out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.79,0:18:52.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was because you didn't want to identify your attacker.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.63,0:18:58.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you said it was Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and then he was found innocent later,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.00,0:19:01.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then all the suspicion would fall onto you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.14,0:19:03.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is all conjecture!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.74,0:19:06.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any evidence that Ichiro's the murderer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.74,0:19:08.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.68,0:19:14.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The piece of bread that was found near Mr. Gozo's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.28,0:19:16.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A piece of bread?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.65,0:19:18.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is an art student.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.65,0:19:21.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And right before Mr. Gozo was murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.69,0:19:23.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he was drawing a picture on the deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.69,0:19:27.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Bread pieces are sometimes used as erasers for charcoal sketches,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.43,0:19:30.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and I hear that these pieces often fall into artists' cuffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.63,0:19:35.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When he stabbed Mr. Gozo, that piece of bread fell out of his cuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.70,0:19:38.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It fell {\i1}onto{\i0} Mr. Gozo's blood, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.91,0:19:42.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, this bread piece has a tiny bit of charcoal on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.94,0:19:46.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no doubt that it was Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} who dropped it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.85,0:19:48.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he has no motive!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.95,0:19:51.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro had no reason to kill Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.42,0:19:55.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I, myself, couldn't tell what his motive was until the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.82,0:19:59.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I saw something in his room, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.39,0:20:01.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Something in his room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.40,0:20:02.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.80,0:20:06.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s motive for killing Mr. Gozo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.60,0:20:10.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How is a picture his motive?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.40,0:20:13.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer is in the drawing itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.27,0:20:15.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see how...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.98,0:20:18.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.15,0:20:19.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.98,0:20:24.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! All these drawings are of Natsue!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.70,0:20:26.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.29,0:20:30.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.53,0:20:35.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was in love with Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.53,0:20:39.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.34,0:20:42.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from Suzuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the butler.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.11,0:20:45.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Unable to reveal your feelings to Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.41,0:20:46.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you went to Mr. Gozo and—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.88,0:20:52.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true! I asked him to let me marry Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.35,0:20:55.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he wouldn't hear me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.49,0:20:58.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He refused to give his beloved Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to someone like me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.56,0:21:01.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And soon after that, almost as if to spite me,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.36,0:21:05.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he announced that Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was going to marry Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.63,0:21:09.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then when he yelled at me yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.27,0:21:12.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while I was on the deck, drawing Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.17,0:21:15.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him to give up his hopeless dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.91,0:21:18.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't forgive them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.01,0:21:22.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not my grandfather, who refused to let me marry Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.01,0:21:28.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nor Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who stole my Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} away from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.24,0:22:57.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takeshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.31,0:23:02.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you still feel the same way toward my grandfather and us?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.71,0:23:05.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}am{\i0} the son of Isao Zaiki,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.01,0:23:10.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who committed suicide after the Hatamoto Group took over his company.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.02,0:23:14.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's true that I got close to you because I hated your grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.16,0:23:17.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But ever since I met you...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.30,0:23:23.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The tragedy was caused by a shy young man
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.97,0:23:27.77,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}who was unable to put his secret thoughts into words...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.07,0:23:32.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The ship is nearing Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.24,0:23:36.42,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}while being bathed by the red sunset that is the sadness and despair
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.42,0:23:38.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}of Ichiro{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} and the entire Hatamoto family.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.24,0:22:24.76,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,NEXT TIME... "THE MISSING SWEETS AT THE OLD SHOP"
